Ricardo L. Cortez, CIMA® 
Co-CEO

As Co-Chief Executive Officer, Mr. Cortez is responsible for the management of Broadmark’s day-to-day business activities as well as the oversight of the firm’s sales and marketing efforts. In addition, he is a member of the Investment Team and serves as the firm’s Chief Risk Officer. Mr. Cortez joined Broadmark in September 2009 as President, Global Distribution and was named Co-CEO in June 2013. Before Broadmark, he was President of the Private Client Group for Torrey Associates, LLC. Additional prior roles include Vice President at Goldman Sachs serving as Product Manager of the firm’s Global Multi-Manager Strategies program, and Senior Vice President with Prudential Investments overseeing product development and sales for the Investment Management Services Division. Mr. Cortez graduated cum laude from Queens College, City University of New York with a B.A. and now serves as Chairman of its Business Advisory Board.  He is also an adjunct faculty member at Harvard University and has been a guest lecturer on Investment Policy and Hedge Funds at the Wharton School, University of Pennsylvania. Mr. Cortez was awarded the Certified Investment Management Analyst® designation in 1993 and is the author of numerous published articles on hedge funds.

Laura A. Hespe

Chief Operating Officer

Ms. Hespe joined Broadmark in January 2000.  Prior to assuming the role of Chief Operating Officer in January 2010, she was Director of Investment Operations, responsible for managing all investment operations and portfolio administration for the firm.  She has over 25 years of experience in the financial industry including five years with Kidder Peabody Asset Management where she became Director of Wrap-Fee Administration.  Immediately prior to joining Broadmark, she was Vice President of McLaughlin Capital Markets, Inc., a Broker/Dealer specializing in institutional equity trading.  There her responsibilities included oversight of Operations, Compliance and Administration.  Ms. Hespe holds a B.S. in Management from the State University of New York at Binghamton. 

Michelle R. da Luz
Director of Investment Operations 

Ms. da Luz joined Broadmark in August 2004. As Investment Operations Director, she is responsible for overseeing post-execution trading operations and portfolio administration.  Prior to becoming Investment Operations Director in 2010, she served as Investment Operations Manager. Ms. da Luz has over 17 years of experience in the financial services and investment industry, including consumer brokerage and advisory services at Citigroup.  She holds a B.S. in Corporate Finance and Financial Services from San Francisco State University, San Francisco. 























