 Advisors & Consultants



Companies ▾




Custodian




Morgan Stanley & Co. LLC


                                    Founded in 1969, Morgan Stanley & Co. LLC is an SEC-registered broker/dealer headquartered in New York City. The firm is the primary broker subsidiary of Morgan Stanley (NYSE: MS). They are a member of FINRA. Morgan Stanley & Co. provides debt and equity services including underwriting, M&A advice, securities dealing and brokerage and trade execution. Their client base ranges from large global institutional investors to hedge funds at the cutting edge of innovation in the industry.The firm's Sales & Trading division offers cash and electronic trading platforms where Morgan Stanley acts as principal (including as a market maker) and agent in executing transactions globally in equity and equity-related products. These products include equity swaps, options, warrants and futures overlying individual securities, indices and baskets of securities and other equity-related products. Morgan Stanley's Institutional Equity division is a global leader in the origination, distribution and trading of equity, equity-linked and equity-derivative securities. Their Fixed Income team deals in a diverse range of products including interest rate and currency products, credit products, derivatives and commodities.                                




Marketer




Forward Management LLC


                                    Forward Management invests in strong, well-managed companies that are trading below their intrinsic value. long-term approach attempts to exploit market inefficiency created by investor emotion or near-term misperceptions. We believe that consistent application of our bottom-up, fundamental, multi-faceted valuation process will provide our clients competitive results with lower volatility in all market environments. The firm's investment strategies span virtually all asset glasses, both domestic and abroad.Forward Management employs bottom-up, fundamental research to identify potential investments. They analyze a company to determine its true worth or intrinsic value, and compare that value to the current market valuation to determine if there is an appropriate margin of safety for investment. Each potential investment must possess solid valuation, strong fundamentals and catalysts which help to validate the underlying investment thesis. They look for companies with low relative p/b, low relative p/e, low relative price-to-cash flow, low relative p/s, low relative EV/EBITDA that are trading below replacement value. Forward Management also seeks companies with strong or improving cash flow, high returns on capital, low relative debt levels and a durable competitive advantage. Key catalysts include management changes, a new product cycle and/or restructuring that improves profitability.                                





