Current Transactions



Broadmark Real Estate Management



$150,000,000 Real Estate Lending Fund

Broadmark Real Estate Management, LLC manages the Broadmark Real Estate Lending Fund II ("BRELF II" or "Fund II"), an unleveraged, no-load, evergreen fund that writes short-term, first position loans secured by real estate in the Mountain West. The goal of the Fund is to provide investors with a high-yield debt instrument while minimizing the risk of principal loss and maintaining near-term liquidity. BRELF II has maintained consistent returns in excess of 11%* annualized since inception due to management's focus on steady and cautious growth.

 

Fact Sheet


Contact Adam Fountain at (206) 623-1200 ext. 120 or afountain@broadmark.com for more information.


Pyatt Broadmark Management, LLC



$250,000,000 Real Estate Lending Fund

Pyatt Broadmark Management, LLC manages the Pyatt Broadmark Real Estate Lending Fund I ("PBRELF I" or "Fund"), an unleveraged, no-load, evergreen fund that writes short-term, first position loans secured by real estate in the Pacific Northwest. The goal of the Fund is to provide investors with a high-yield debt instrument while minimizing the risk of principal loss and maintaining near-term liquidity. PBRELF I has maintained consistent returns in excess of 11%* annualized since inception due to management's focus on steady and cautious growth.

Fact Sheet

 
 


Contact Adam Fountain at (206) 623-1200 ext. 120 or afountain@broadmark.com for more information.



